HEADWORD: Duchesse lace
<hw>Du`chesse" lace</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A beautiful variety of
Brussels pillow lace made originally in Belgium and resembling Honiton
guipure. It is worked with fine thread in large sprays, usually of the
primrose pattern, with much raised work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duchy</ent>⟦br⟧
